title: Free Trade Zones: What are the challenges for Workers in Sri Lanka?
description: Following the Global Dialogue Forum on Wages and Working Hours in the Textiles, Clothing, Leather and Footwear Industries held in Geneva from 23 - 25 September 2014,  Anton Marcus, Joint Secretary of Free Zones and General Services Employees Union, explains the challenges facing by workers in Free Trade Zones in Sri Lanka.  He also underlines the role of ILO to improve social dialogue and collective bargaining in Sri Lanka.
tags: Free Trade Zone', 'Trade Union (Organization Type)', 'Workers', 'Sri Lanka (Country)'
